        ? `Spondylosis is often asymptomatic, meaning many people may have the condition without experiencing pain or discomfort. When symptoms do occur, they vary depending on the region of the spine affected. <br/><br/>
    <strong class='text-white'>Cervical Spondylosis (neck):</strong> The most common symptoms include neck pain and stiffness, which may worsen with activity. It's common to experience headaches, especially at the back of the head, and a grinding sensation when turning the neck. <br/><br/>
